<h1>NRCAR PART 2031 - CONTRACT COST PRINCIPLES AND PROCEDURES</h1>
<hr size="2" width="80%"><p><a href="2031.html" name="LOC_P0_0">PART 2031 - CONTRACT COST PRINCIPLES AND PROCEDURES</a></p>

  <ul><li><a href="2031.html" name="LOC_P2_115">Subpart 2031.1 Applicability</a></li>

  <ul><ul><li><a href="2031.html" name="LOC_P3_143">ยง2031.109-70 Contract clauses.</a></li></ul></ul></ul><hr size="2" width="80%"><!-- TRANSIT - TEXTBAR --><p><a name="P0_0"></a><font size="+1"><b>PART 2031 - CONTRACT COST PRINCIPLES AND PROCEDURES</b></font></p>

<p>AUTHORITY: 42 U.S.C. 2201; 42 U.S.C. 5841; and 41 U.S.C. 418(b).</p>

<p align="center"><a name="P2_115"></a><font size="+1"><b>Subpart 2031.1 Applicability</b></font></p>

<p><a name="P3_143"></a><font size="+1"><b>ยง2031.109-70 Contract clauses.</b></font></p>

<p>The contracting officer shall insert the clause at <font color="#0000ff" size="+1"><u><!-- TRANSIT - HYPERLINK --><!-- .2052.doc#s205223170. --><a href="2052.html">ยง2052.231-70</a></u></font>, Precontract Costs, in all cost type contracts when costs in connection with work under the contract will be incurred by the contractor before the effective date of the contract. Approval for use of this clause must be obtained at one level above the contracting officer.</p>
